-- Egypt Prepares to Offer $3 Billion of Joint Projects, Borsa Says
-- B y   T a r e k   E l - T a b l a w y
-- 2012-10-15T06:04:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-15/egypt-prepares-to-offer-3-billion-of-joint-projects-borsa-says.html
Egypt  is preparing to offer four
public-private partnership infrastructure projects with a
projected investment of $3 billion in fiscal 2012-2013, Al-Borsa
reported today citing Investment Minister Osama Saleh.  The ministry is nearing the completion of feasibility
studies for a new water plant in southern Egypt, Saleh said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tarek El-Tablawy in Cairo at 
 teltablawy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 